# PROJECT: slint-gui-mcp

## Goal
A Windows-only MCP server written in Rust that gives AI assistants (e.g. Claude Code) vision
and control of a running GUI window. It reduces GUI guesswork by providing direct visual
feedback and image-based interaction through template matching rather than hard-coded
coordinates.

## Stack
- Language: Rust (stable, edition 2021)
- MCP protocol: rmcp 0.1 (server + transport-io features)
- Window capture: windows crate 0.58 (Win32 HWND-based)
- Image processing: image 0.25, imageproc 0.25
- Input: Windows messaging plus focused window control
- Serialization: serde 1, serde_json 1, base64 0.22
- Async runtime: tokio 1
- Build scanners: rustdocumenter, rustscanners

## Structure
- binary entry: src/main.rs
- crate root: src/lib.rs
- UI layer: src/ui/
- adapter layer: src/adapter/
- core layer: src/core/
- platform layer: src/pal/
- shared errors and support: src/shared/
- constants and limits: src/state/
- tests: tests/
- docs: doc/
- project control: proj/

## Method
- Workflow: PROJECT -> FIXES -> TODO -> code -> cargo build -> cargo test -> DONE
- Branching: feature branches, never commit to main
- Testing: cargo test
- Deploy: single binary, no runtime dependencies

## Patterns
- window-find: partial case-insensitive title match -> HWND
- image-capture: Win32 capture -> BGRA buffer -> RgbImage -> PNG/base64
- template-match: normalized cross-correlation (NCC) over RGB images
- mcp-tool: #[tool(tool_box)] on server struct, one async fn per MCP tool
- adapter-dispatch: ui -> adapter -> core/pal
- constants: thresholds, timings, buffer sizes in src/state/

## Current
